\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Re-affirmation on the receptor-low (TNBC-like) subset.} The Setup A static controller (ranked) on the full cohort (teal) and on the receptor-low subset (gold), the latter defined by low ESR1, PGR, and ERBB2 in the binarised data as a transcriptomic proxy for triple-negative status. Individual phenotypes remain highly controllable in the subset while the joint all-three rate stays in the low single digits, the same individual-versus-joint pattern as in the full cohort. Subset sizes: TCGA 237 (22\%), METABRIC 363 (18\%), I-SPY2 279 (28\%).}}{13}{figure.caption.14}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:tnbc}{{2}{13}{\textbf {Re-affirmation on the receptor-low (TNBC-like) subset.} The Setup A static controller (ranked) on the full cohort (teal) and on the receptor-low subset (gold), the latter defined by low ESR1, PGR, and ERBB2 in the binarised data as a transcriptomic proxy for triple-negative status. Individual phenotypes remain highly controllable in the subset while the joint all-three rate stays in the low single digits, the same individual-versus-joint pattern as in the full cohort. Subset sizes: TCGA 237 (22\%), METABRIC 363 (18\%), I-SPY2 279 (28\%)}{figure.caption.14}{}}
